<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 15984/13.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-17"><hi rend="italic">December 17,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Abe case. Favorable action by court Dalny. Prisoner being conveyed
                            Yokohama for delivery to Hawaiian officer on board steamship <hi rend="italic">China</hi> sailing 23d.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">O’Brien.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>